sql:
SELECT two_dose_rate
FROM vaccination_data
ORDER BY date DESC;

external_knowledge:
A 'single dose' refers to the first dose in a series of vaccinations, and the eligibility criteria include age groups '16+' and '30+';
A high one-dose rate indicates good vaccination coverage in a jurisdiction;
An eligible population greater than 500,000 signifies a significant number of people who can receive vaccinations in a jurisdiction.

sql:
SELECT eligible_population
FROM population_eligibility
WHERE age_group = '16+' AND booster_shot_type = 'Pfizer';

SELECT SUM(eligible_population) AS total_eligible_population
FROM population_eligibility
WHERE jurisdiction_id = 0 AND age_group = '16+';

external_knowledge:
/top-level jurisdictions; refers to jurisdictions with no parent_id; 
hierarchical structure; the level of a jurisdiction determines its position in the hierarchy; 
recent vaccination and eligibility data; the most recent data available is considered; 
this data is ordered by the level of the jurisdiction in the hierarchy and then alphabetically by jurisdiction name.

sql:
SELECT jurisdiction_name 
FROM jurisdictions 
WHERE parent_jurisdiction_id IS NULL;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS num_large_jurisdictions
FROM jurisdictions
WHERE population > 10000000;

SELECT jurisdiction_name 
FROM jurisdictions 
ORDER BY jurisdiction_name;

SELECT jurisdiction_name
FROM jurisdictions
WHERE jurisdiction_type = 'national';
